rComments: Professeure passionnée et dévouée pour ses étudiants . Son approche est à la fois humaine et rigoureuse. J'ai beaucoup appris et j'ai adoré sa façon de nous faire réfléchir et explorer différentes approches en psychologie.

She lost multiple exams and assignments. She tried to change the weight of our work and the head of the department had to intervene to ensure she followed the syllabus. She also asked us to complete psychological test (Briggs Myers) and forced us to include our names. We had assignments during class that were to long for any of us to complete.

Meilleure prof que j'ai eu pendant tout mon bacc! Elle est tellement dévouée et passionnée pour son travail. Elle donne toujours de bons exemples concrets pour élaborer la matière. Facile de gagner des points avec les quiz. Et elle est toujours disponible pour répondre à nos questions ou même simplement pour jaser et apprendre à nous connaître.

Everyone got different grading criterias for the oral presentation and it ended up that no one understood what she wanted. She teaches you about deontology, but she does not respect it herself. Very subjective about how she grades you and you need to verify carefully your exams and make sure she gave you the good grade. DON'T TAKE HER COURSE!

If you want to lower your Gpa, dont take any course with this prof. 1. you will learn nothing. 2. She will manage to make the course content seem very very very awful. She's the one awful. She will teach you nothing, and at the end of the semester, she will smash you with a very hard exam, with very specific questions. You will not even understand.

Her descriptions for projects are one or two lines, so its hard to figure out her specific guidelines... if there are NO SPECIFIC GUIDELINES.  Graded quiz after every class, oral presentation at the end of the semester, papers due every week. All from the book. Everything. Study everything. Everythinnnnnggggggggg. Or fail, your choice.

She is terrible. She wins by far the worst professor I've had in university. She doesn't know her course material, she reads off her  slides that are plagiarized from the book. Her exam questions are from random parts of the book. She doesn't aswer questions, instead she asks us to google it. Absolutely awful.

Je trouve cela dommage, car la prof est gentille et elle est drôle, mais elle ne lit que les powerpoints.  Je trouve ça trop des quizz et des travaux d'équipe prèsque à chaque cours. Facile de perdre beaucoup de point si on doit s'absenter. Examens difficile à passer car c'est seulement du par coeur...

Very little course content, but enormous exams (for some reason, that makes it so they have stupid questions). Half the lectures aren't even lectures, they're discussion groups, meaning even less course content. She explains everything very well, but goes off on huge tangents that don't contribute to student learning. Really nice, but not great.

Good prof who cares about her student. Assignments may seem intimidating at first but they're easy to get through if you pay attention in class. She's always available to answer questions. Exams aren't easy so make sure you study well. Lots of trends!!!
Had her for women psych! She outlines the class to encourage group discussion. The group discussion work make it generally easy to receive good grades. Interesting reading material.

Had her for psychologie clinique! If youre interested in pursuing psychology i highly recommend this course with her. She clearly loves her job and has a lot of experience as a psychologist. Really lets you see what a job in psychology entails.

Really sweet prof. She makes time for and cares about if her students understand the content. Easy 16% if you show up for the discussion groups, lectures always end around 8:30 but with discussions its more like 9. Gives outlines for exams so you know exactly what to study.

This prof gives you every single topic for the questions used on the exam AND she offers 2 extra credit assignments. Her classes consist of content review from the textbook, group discussions and group presentations that are graded by the class. She is there for her students, willing to answer any question, and she is super funny and nice!

C'est comme ci elle ne prenait pas le temps de nous enseigner come il faut. Elle était plus intéressé à nous faire participer dans des activités inutiles que de nous enseigner la matière et c'était hyper frustrant. J'étais excitée pour ce cours mais j'en suis sortie pas mal découragée. Pas pour être méchante, mais évitez ce prof.

Be prepared to teach yourself if you take her class. A lot of people describe her down here as sweet but in terms of teaching she's completely inadequate unfortunately. I wouldn't mind that if she pulled all her information from our textbook, but a lot of concepts aren't taught properly and we're expected to just figure it out on our own. Annoying

If you're good at memorization, this is the class for you. Simple, organized slideshows and an easy 16% of your mark is made up of attendance quizzes. Sweet woman who really knows her stuff. People say that the guidelines are iffy about the group presentation but just remember to link your topic back to the psychology of women and you'll be fine.

Really great prof. Easy marks with group discussions every class and a group project. Tells interesting stories that relates to the content. Gave a list for what topics would specifically be on the exams. Very sweet
Definitely pay attention and use your textbook for further clarification. Overall good teacher, respectful and understanding - would recommend.

La prof ne connaît pas du tout sa matière. Énormément de fautes factuelles dans son powerpoint qu'elle se contente de lire. Elle base son cours sur un manuel d'une édition passée et nous pénalise parce que nous nous fions à l'édition qu'elle nous a demandé d'acheter. Incapable de répondre à des questions en classe. Examens sont que du par coeur.

Put WAY too much emphasis on group discussions. Instead of taking her time to explain concepts and make sure we understood, she wasted our time by making us fill in these "group discussions" that were all based on a completely different textbook! I wouldn't recommend taking this class if you actually want to learn something. Avoid her.

Decent professor, can be boring and move through topics a little to quickly at times but overall she is a good teacher. Activities at the end of each lecture are very helpful to ensure you understand the material. Easy to talk to if you need help. Group project is fairly easy and fun to do.

I always felt super frustrated in this class... Like she never really explained concepts and she would tell us to "google" stuff. We also had no idea what to expect from her most of the time. I feel like like I didn't learn a thing in her class. She might be "nice" but she's a terrible prof. I recommend taking Dr. Terry Howard's section over hers.
Dr. Girard is honestly really caring and thoughtful. She's there if you need help outside class and she's extremely accommodating. Would take her class again, I'm not just saying that.

Elle ne connait PAS sa matière. On lui pose des questions et elle répond n'importe quoi, car elle ne le sait pas plus que nous. Les réponses des quiz sont contradictoires avec la matière. Les PP sont des copiers/collés du manuel et elle nous a fait acheter la mauvais édition, alors tout se contredit. Elle lit les power point sans explications.
Good prof! Clear expectations of what will be covered in class! Loves psychology and has cool clinical stories.

Horrible. Graded group assignments every single class, and a group presentation at the end of the semester. Her slides are taken directly from the textbook... And her midterm (100 multiple choice questions) is so long. Not to mention she's blatantly rude to her students. She needs to calm down.

Every class includes one quiz, before and after the material. It is mostly based on the book, but she gets mad if you aren't paying attention. Tough grader, will switch one word and try to trick you. She gives revisions but then in class will say things that are on the exam that weren't on her revision sheets. Confusing.

Great professor who really cares about her students. I loved going to class. She really wants you to succeed. Grades aren't easy to get but it's expected of a third year class. Would take another class with her.
Nice professor

C'est un cours de difficulté moyenne.  Lorsqu'elle enseigne on comprend bien la manière. Il y a des discussions de groupes presque chaque cours qui sont notés. Il y aussi un travail à faire sur une femme.

WORST TEACHER IVE EVER HAD. and ive had my fair share of bad ones. insults you personally and class as a whole, EXTREMELY SUBJECTIVE. has no marking scheme. long papers every single week to hand in, powerpoints are the least clear thing youve ever read, exams are full of mistakes. made my semester a misery.

Très ouverte, facile d'approche, toujours prête à aider, les examens sont mots pour mots ce qui est dans ses power point, donc facile d'avoir des bonnes notes mais impossible de réussir en manquant des cours.
BEST PROF EVER!!!

The textbook contradicted itself like 1,000 times and she refuses to give you a better mark on midterms quizzes every class at the beginning. Even if the answer is right in the book, her language barrier words midterms and quiz questions in a different manner than what she wants you to answer. I would not take this course with her.

She was super kind and obviously cared about her students. Each class had 2 quizzes and discussion at the end for marks, so it was essential to go to each class to get full marks. The midterm and exam were easy if you had read the textbook.

Prof Girard is super easy going and very approachable. She is extremely helpful and undertstanding. Answers e-mails within the hour (most times). Participation was marked in quick group assignments during every class. She gave us the questions for our midtermexam in  advance and the rubric for the written assignment was given on day one.

She was very nice and approachable. A lot of people had problems with her because her marking sometimes was unfair. She has very vague description for assignments and the presentation. Wasn't a bad course and it wasn't that hard to get a pretty good mark.

Ne pas prendre ce cours: c'est déprimant et plate. On ne fait que lire un livre et l'apprendre par coeur (mots pour mots, c'est tellement pas pédagogique. La seule façon qu'elle arrive a garder ses étudiants c'est en racontant sa vie personnelle et par les quiz pondératifs dans lesquels  il est difficile d'avoir de bonnes notes.

LOVED HER! She keeps her class interesting, and very clear. She got rid of the final paper, so whatever concerns others had, it's gooone! haha. Take her class, if you enjoy psychology and learning new things!

NE PAS PRENDRE CE COURS! Examens à choix de réponses de 100 questions!! Et son travail de mi session est extrêmement pas clair, 10-12 pages Elle évalue très mal ses travaux! Elle nous a dit "parce que vous avez eu une bonne moyenne dans le 1er examen je serai sévère pour le travail" GROSSE MARDE!
Overall I think she is great! She uses a lot of powerpoints which are directly from the book so make sure you study those. Her tests are very fair and she give hints too :)
A lot of group works, but a very good teacher. Always there for her students. Really easy exams, just learn the powerpoints.

A lot of group work, quizzes, & a presentation (resminscent of a college course). Ask for clarity. Don't assume to know what she is looking for based on written instruction alone. Some thrive in this environment, others don't. Consider what's best for you based on your perfered evaluation method. If it's exams I would suggest another section.

She is good-natured but she can not teach. Her slides are taken directly from the book which are read during class. Boring discussions every week. Odd project which I still haven't understood. Gets angry when wanting to discuss grades. On the plus side she replies to her emails fast and is a fast marker. But I would not take another class with her.

She makes her "notes" from the book, but they tend to be very vague/incomplete, so you need the book. The research paper directions were also very vague, and she tends to change her mind on certain things she wants in the assignment. Also, she can be pretty rude sometimes, especially talking about grades. I say good luck to people who have her.

Brutal. Quizzes every class that you cannot prepare for even if you try and uses them as attendance. Loses your assignments. Incomprehensible instructions. Incomplete syllabus. Managed a B+ but she makes it really hard to do better than that. Emailed her regarding some incorrect grades and she was so rude to me! Avoid!!!!

PSY: 2510 Elle lit les power points qui sont VRAIMENT long! Mais elle est super gentille et repond au questions. Elle donne EACTEMENT les sujets de l'examen. Elle fait l'examen en ordre chronologique de la feuille de révision (donc c'est une très bonne idée d'étudier chronologiquement!)

Mon dieu....J'ai jamais eu un esti de bon prof comme lui! Je vous encourage fortement de prendre ce cours! Auparavant, j'ai détesté la recherche, mais à cause d'elle et sa motivation la recherche n'est plus une notion qui fait peur. Elle fait rire, en plus elle comprends très bien ses étudiants, soit anglophone ou francophone. Très hot en passant!

DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS. the friggin exams are impossible and the midterm essay to hand in has the most incomprehensible directives to follow ever. Do yourself a favor: DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS!! Attendance is mandatory too!!!!

Doesn't explain anything in class. Power points are just copy-paste from the book. She says the exam is based on "recognizing the main ideas of topics" but it's not true. You literally have to learn everything, word for word, if you want a good mark. Avoid if possible.
Présence obligatoire, n'explique rien sur ses powerpoints qu'elle ne fait que lire !

À ne PAS prendre! Elle a des powerpoints avec ex 1 phrase: La théorie de Bem. Elle dit : Donc Bem a eu une grande influence sur la psychologie sociale. Et elle change de diapo! Hellooo ça te tente pas d'expliquer la théorie de Bem? Elle n'enseigne strictement rien, c'est de loin la prof la moins compétente que j'ai eu. Lisez le manuel absolument!

I don't understand how the university of Ottawa afford these low quality teachers; they might know the material but they are the worst in giving the information to students; do yourself a favor: DO NOT take a course with her

Horrible professor. She makes the students grade the students, and just reads the slides. I regret taking this class. She is  most certainly the worst educator I have ever had. I absolutely do NOT recommend her class. The course is interesting but she makes the material very boring and useless.
I had her for psychology of women. I think she was a good professor.

Would be a fairly easy class but the final assignment is very unclear (strange marking scheme) and changes are often made at the last minute. I would suggest going to see her for an indepth meeting regarding the project but she has no office on campus and very little time to meet with students. easy weekly quizzes and attendence.
Les explications ne sont pas claires et sont souvent donner à la dernière minute. des changement au niveau du projet à la dernière minute est à considéré.
First time I Ace a psychology class! Really easy to get an A in this class and super easy and straight-forward exams. final project, though, was too much work!

Very unclear in her expectations. Mandatory attendance even though her notes are online and straight out of the text. Lots of small, pointless group work in class (worth 20%). Final assignment ok, but with very unclear expectations. She is almost incapable of expanding on text material or having an original thought.
Exams are very easy. Just like the notes and the textbook. No surprises there. However, the paper/presentation requirements are very vague. Seek clarification before you start your project.

Very open to suggestion, sometimes confusing when describing evaluation for presentations (and what is required). Very keen/interested in her subject matter, which is key. Evaluations are fair, but class attendance is mandatory, and book is used A LOT for exam studying. She wants the students to do well.

She heavily relies on her slides. The majority if not all her answers are found in the textbook and often word for word. 60% of the class was spent watching group presentations instead of learning; an unfortunately waste of time. A potentially interesting class....potentially....

Spent the whole time watching presentations...hard to negotiate...she will never accept when she has made a mistake and will often go back on her word and blame the student if she finds that the result is not "up to her standards." All in all, another interesting topic that had much potential.
Great prof! Super friendly, helpful, and always available.  The only psych prof I actually made a point to take another class with.

Cette femme n'enseigne pas! Elle te dis quel pages lire et parle de elle pendant près de 3 hrs. Je n'ai appris avec elle et je ne comprend pas comment quelqu'un comme ca peut avoir fait pour complèter un bac!! La pire des pires! C'est elle!
good teacher.
Très accomodante et comprehensive.  Exemples et annecdotes interessants, activites stimulantes. Bonne note assurer si la preparation de l'examen est fait convenablement.
Good prof, takes her courses seriously in terms of research.  Good orator as well, straight forward evaluations
very clear and nice.  she really takes her time to help her students

yes, it is easy to get a good grade with her & she practically gives out the questions beforehand, but she should take us more seriously and give a tougher course in which we actually learn stuff. she is nice but i felt cheated out of quality education.
Excellent prof, very helpful.
very nice but all you do in her class is watch movies. Could be a good way to learn for some but i almost failed this class because of her lack of teaching skills.
Obviously, this professor should not be teaching. Yes, it is very easy to obtain great marks with her but NO, I did not learn anything.
She obviously does not enjoy teaching...  she should just stick to her clinical job.
She does give many helpful hints for the exams, very helpful and polite to her students. A recommend her to anyone who wishes to take a psych course.
She almost reads the exam in class!
If you like watching movies, take this course
Very good review prior to exam.
